column2: It rained yesterday and today is sunny.  This was the day before the flood in June of 2008.  The water beneath the bridge was clear and high.

The day was hot.  The lagoon filled with garbage including a garbage wire can.  The litter was in the reeds and along the bank.  The water was unusually high like it was not draining and appeared milky not at all like earlier in the year.  The geese present but also ducks were not in large numbers.  The water was so high that where I usually stood was under water. Cool- occasionally cloudy past two days.  High and very milky water.  Dirty bank- garbage can in lagoon.
Overcast- light rain- Canadian Geese. Overcast- light rain- Canadian Geese.
